Then commutation relations, which include spinor generators, read
\begin{eqnarray}\label{AdS20}
&\left\{ Q, {\overline Q}{} \right\} =2P, \;  \left\{ S, {\overline S}{} \right\} =2P -4 m J, \; \left\{ Q, S \right\} =2{\overline Z}{}, \; \left\{ {\overline Q}{}, {\overline S}{}\right\} =2Z,& {\nonumber} \\
&\left[ Z, Q\right] = -2m {\overline S}{}, \; \left[ {\overline Z}{}, {\overline Q}{}\right] = 2m S, \; \left[ Z, S \right] = -2m {\overline Q}{}, \; \left[ {\overline Z}{}, {\overline S}{} \right] = 2m Q,& {\nonumber} \\
&\left[ P, S\right] = -2m S, \; \left[ P, {\overline S}{}\right] = 2m {\overline S}{}, &\\
&\left[ T,Q  \right]=-{\overline S}{}, \; \left[ {\overline T}{}, {\overline Q}{}\right] = S, \; \left[ T, S\right] = - {\overline Q}{}, \; \left[ {\overline T}{}, {\overline S}{} \right] = Q,&{\nonumber} \\
&\left[ J_3, Q\right] = -\frac{1}{2}Q, \; \left[ J_3, {\overline Q}{}\right] = \frac{1}{2}{\overline Q}{}, \; \left[ J_3, S\right] = -\frac{1}{2}S, \; \left[ J_3, {\overline S}{}\right] = \frac{1}{2}{\overline S}{},&{\nonumber} \\
