\subsection{Supersymmetric nonrelativistic Newton-Hooke particle}
It is possible to construct a nonrelativistic version of the $N=(2,0)$ supersymmetric AdS$_3$ algebra and the corresponding superparticle actions.
Remembering our rescaling of the bosonic subalgebra {(\ref{{rescale2}})} and preserving the unbroken supersymmetry, one can  not rescale the generators $Q,{\overline Q}{}$. In addition, for keeping the relation $\big\{ Q, S  \big\} = 2{\overline Z}{}$ in order to realize some sort of inverse Higgs effect, it is required to rescale the $S$-generator as $S \rightarrow \omega S$. Performing such a rescaling and taking the limit $\omega \rightarrow \infty$, we  obtain the following superalgebra,
\begin{eqnarray}\label{SUSYNHooke}
&& \big\{ Q,{\overline Q}{} \big\} = 2 P, \quad, \big\{Q, S\} =2 {\overline Z}{}, \quad \big\{ {\overline Q}{} , {\overline S}{}  \big\} = 2Z, \quad \big\{ S,{\overline S}{}  \big\} =-4m J, {\nonumber} \\
&& \big[ Z, Q    \big] = -2 m{\overline S}{}, \quad \big[ {\overline Z}{}, {\overline Q}{} \big] = 2m S, \quad \big[ P, S \big] = -2 mS, \quad \big[ P, {\overline S}{} \big] = 2m {\overline S}{},   \\
&& \big[ T, Q   \big] = -{\overline S}{}, \quad \big[ {\overline T}{}, {\overline Q}{}   \big] = S, \quad \big[ T, P \big] = -Z , \quad \big[ {\overline T}{}, P\big] = {\overline Z}{}, \quad \big[ P, Z \big] =2 m Z, \quad \big[ P, {\overline Z}{} \big] = -2 m{\overline Z}{},  {\nonumber} \\
&& \big[ T, {\overline T}{}  \big] =-2J_3,\quad \big[ T,{\overline Z}{}\big] = -2 m J, \quad \big[ {\overline T}{}, Z \big] =2m J, \quad \big[ Z,{\overline Z}{}\big] = 4 m^2 J,{\nonumber}
\end{eqnarray}
where the generators $J$ and $J_3$ are still central elements of the superalgebra.

The coset element can be parameterized as before {(\ref{{coset}})},

