To construct the invariant supersymmetric actions generalizing the bosonic actions {(\ref{{action1}})}, {(\ref{{anyonu}})}, {(\ref{{rigid}})}, we must investigate $S$ and $Q$ supersymmetries.
It is not hard to check that these actions are $S$-invariant but not $Q$-invariant.  Thus, one has to find fermionic completions invariant
under $Q$ supersymmetry. It is rather easy to see that the following fermionic actions,
\begin{eqnarray}\label{SUSYredact}
&& S_0^{ferm} =  \int dt \left[ {\rm i} \big( \dot\psi {\bar\psi}{} + \dot{\bar\psi}{} \psi \big)+ 4m \psi{\bar\psi}{} \right], \\
